  "prompt": "How much cubic meter of cement, sand required for 12mm cement sand plaster 1:6 for 950 sq m?",
  "response": "To determine the required quantities of cement and sand for plastering a **950 square meter** area with a **12mm thickness** using a **1:6 mix ratio (cement : sand)**, follow these steps:\n\n### 1. Calculate the Total Volume of Plaster\n\n**Plaster Thickness:** 12 mm = 0.012 meters  \n**Surface Area:** 950 m\u00b2\n\n\\[\n\\text{Volume} = \\text{Area} \\times \\text{Thickness} = 950 \\, \\text{m}\u00b2 \\times 0.012 \\, \\text{m} = 11.4 \\, \\text{m}\u00b3\n\\]\n\n### 2. Apply the Mix Ratio\n\nThe mix ratio **1:6** means:\n\n- **1 part cement**\n- **6 parts sand**\n\n**Total parts** = 1 (cement) + 6 (sand) = **7 parts**\n\n#### a. Cement Required\n\n\\[\n\\text{Cement Volume} = \\left( \\frac{1}{7} \\right) \\times 11.4 \\, \\text{m}\u00b3 \\approx 1.63 \\, \\text{m}\u00b3\n\\]\n\n#### b. Sand Required\n\n\\[\n\\text{Sand Volume} = \\left( \\frac{6}{7} \\right) \\times 11.4 \\, \\text{m}\u00b3 \\approx 9.77 \\, \\text{m}\u00b3\n\\]\n\n### 3. Summary of Requirements\n\n- **Cement:** Approximately **1.63 cubic meters**\n- **Sand:** Approximately **9.77 cubic meters**\n\n### 4. Additional Considerations\n\n- **Wastage:** It's advisable to account for a **5-10%** wastage due to spillage, mixing losses, etc.\n  \n  - **Cement with 10% wastage:**  \n    \\[\n    1.63 \\, \\text{m}\u00b3 \\times 1.10 \\approx 1.79 \\, \\text{m}\u00b3\n    \\]\n  \n  - **Sand with 10% wastage:**  \n    \\[\n    9.77 \\, \\text{m}\u00b3 \\times 1.10 \\approx 10.75 \\, \\text{m}\u00b3\n    \\]\n\n- **Final Recommended Quantities:**\n  - **Cement:** ~1.8 m\u00b3\n  - **Sand:** ~10.8 m\u00b3\n\n### 5. Converting Cubic Meters to Bags (Optional)\n\nIf you prefer to estimate using cement bags:\n\n- **1 cubic meter of cement** \u2248 **6-7 bags** (assuming each bag is **50 kg**)\n  \n  \\[\n  1.8 \\, \\text{m}\u00b3 \\times 6.5 \\, \\text{bags/m}\u00b3 \\approx 11.7 \\, \\text{bags}\n  \\]\n  \n  So, approximately **12 bags of cement** are needed.\n\n### 6. Final Note\n\nEnsure that the preparation and application are done correctly to achieve the desired plaster quality. It's also recommended to consult with a local supplier or contractor for precise measurements based on site-specific conditions.\n\n---\n\n**Summary:**\n- **Cement Required:** ~1.63 m\u00b3 (approximately 12 bags)\n- **Sand Required:** ~9.77 m\u00b3\n\nAccounting for wastage, you might consider ordering about **1.8 m\u00b3 of cement** and **10.8 m\u00b3 of sand**.",
